					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Yes, this ground would be near the CAN pins, so theoretically should be closer to the transceiver GND on both ends.  So less potential noise sources in-between, is my reasoning, I dunno if it's sound. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />  Of course it's still connected to the same ground as everything else, it's just in addition to that.
<br />
<br />Cart GND pins are on the far ends of the board, and the CAN transceiver should be as close to the pin as possible (so it'll end up in the middle, above the EXP pins).</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

