				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">OK I know that usually the sound for the powerpak is passed through EXP7 (pin 53) because that's what official MMC5 carts used.
<br />
<br />However, the toploader does NOT have that pin. Only EXP0,3,4,5,8,9 (pins 19,20,51,52,55) are present (they are just left disconnected).
<br />
<br />So if one of those pins were assigned to a second sound pin, and that an update of the powerpak would send the sound to both pin 53 and one of those, then it would be possible to get expansion audio on a toploader NES. Otherwise.... you'll have a hard time ading a pin in the connector.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Life is complex: it has both real and imaginary components.</div>
					<br clear="all" /><br />

